It seems that static constructors are _guaranteed to have completed_, almost. 

Static constructors can be called explicitly with [`RuntimeHelpers.RunClassConstructor`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.runtime.compilerservices.runtimehelpers.runclassconstructor?view=netframework-4.8) which &#39;_Ensures that the type initializer (also known as a static constructor) for the specified type has been run&#39;_.

In your example, the code could be written as follows. 

